                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/41: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Fortes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-28T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 28, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Department’s circular June 27, 7 p.m. I have taken up the subject matter of
                    the Department’s instruction with the Foreign Minister who viewed it very
                    sympathetically. The Foreign Minister is referring it to the President upon the
                    latter’s return.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
